.TH CUPIDWMCTL 1 VERSION
.SH NAME
cupidwmctl \- local IPC control client for cupidwm
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cupidwmctl
.RB [ \-s " path" ]
.RB [ \-\-json ]
.RB [ \-\-print\-socket ]
.RI <command ...>
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cupidwmctl
connects to cupidwm's optional local UNIX socket IPC server and sends a
single command.
IPC is disabled by default in
.IR config.h ;
enable it with
.I ipc_enable
before using this tool.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-s \fIpath\fR
Use an explicit socket path.
.TP
.B \-\-json
Request JSON-formatted replies.
.TP
.B \-\-print\-socket
Print the resolved socket path and exit.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print usage information and exit.
.SH SOCKET DISCOVERY
Socket resolution order:
.IP 1.
Explicit
.B \-s
path
.IP 2.
.B CUPIDWM_IPC_SOCKET
environment variable
.IP 3.
Hint file in
.B $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR
written by a running cupidwm instance
.IP 4.
Built-in default path rules
.PP
Default socket path rules:
.IP 1.
.B $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/cupidwm-\fIdisplay\fR.sock
.RB ( or
.B cupidwm.sock
if
.B DISPLAY
is unavailable)
.IP 2.
.B /tmp/cupidwm-\fIuid\fR/cupidwm-\fIdisplay\fR.sock
.RB ( or
.B /tmp/cupidwm-\fIuid\fR/cupidwm.sock
if
.B DISPLAY
is unavailable)
.PP
When cupidwm uses the
.B /tmp
fallback, it requires the per-user directory to be private and owned by the
current user.
.SH COMMANDS
Supported commands include:
.TP
.B ping
Health check. Replies with
.BR "ok pong" .
.TP
.B help
Print the server's command summary.
.TP
.B status
Return workspace, monitor, focused window, and layout state.
.TP
.B subscribe
Keep the socket open and stream events (use
.B \-\-json
for JSON event lines).
.TP
.B focus next
Focus the next managed client on the current workspace.
.TP
.B focus prev
Focus the previous managed client on the current workspace.
.TP
.BI "workspace " N
Switch to workspace
.IR N " (1-9)."
.TP
.BI "move-workspace " N
Move the focused client to workspace
.IR N " (1-9)."
.TP
.BI "workspace-name set " N " name"
Set the displayed name for workspace
.IR N .
.TP
.BI "workspace-name clear " N
Reset workspace
.I N
to its configured default name.
.TP
.B workspace-name get
Show all workspace names.
.TP
.BI "workspace-name get " N
Show the name for workspace
.IR N .
.TP
.BI "layout " name
Set the current layout. Supported names:
.BR tile ,
.BR monocle ,
.BR floating ,
.BR fibonacci ,
.BR dwindle ,
.BR grid ,
.BR columns .
.TP
.B reload
Reload configuration from
.IR config.h .
.TP
.B quit
Terminate cupidwm cleanly.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
cupidwmctl ping
cupidwmctl status
cupidwmctl --json query clients
cupidwmctl --json subscribe
cupidwmctl workspace 3
cupidwmctl layout monocle
cupidwmctl workspace-name set 3 coding
CUPIDWM_IPC_SOCKET=/path/to/cupidwm.sock cupidwmctl status
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B cupidwmctl
returns non-zero on argument errors, socket resolution failures, connect
failures, or when the server returns no reply.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR cupidwm (1),
.BR xprop (1)
